<HEADLINE> Kabila Says Africa's Future Promising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Laurant Kabila, president of the
Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), said here Saturday that
Africa's prospects are hopeful, the Algerian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after the conclusion of the 35th summit
of the Organization of African Unity (OAU), Kabila also stressed
his desire to enhance the ties between his country and Algeria.
</P>
<P>
He hailed his talks with Algerian President Abdelaziz
Bouteflika on the sidelines of the OAU summit as "fruitful."
</P>
<P>
Many resolutions have been taken towards the right direction
during the OAU summit, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Heads of states and governments from 45 countries participated
in the OAU summit on July 12-14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
