<HEADLINE> Saudi, Venezuelan Officials Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabian Petroleum and Mineral
Wealth Minister Ali Bin Ibrahim al-N'aimi met in Jeddah Saturday
with visiting Venezuelan Deputy Foreign Minister Khorkhi Valero
Pristivio.
</P>
<P>
Saudi News Agency (SNA) said the two sides discussed ways of
stepping up cooperation among oil producing countries, Saudi
Arabia and Venezuela in particular.
</P>
<P>
In remarks to the SNA, al-N'aimi stressed the oil cooperation
between the two members of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries, also two of the world's leading oil producers and
exporters.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the recent improvement in oil prices in
world markets was the result of the co-ordination among
oil-producing countries including Saudi Arabia and Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
Crude oil price in London on Thursday exceeded 19 U.S. dollars a
barrel for the September contracts while in New York it hit 20
dollar per barrel. 
</P>
