<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy's Commesso Wins 13th Stage at Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Salvatore Commesso won the
13th stage, the longest stage in the Tour de France cycling race
over 236.5 kilometers from St Flour to Albi, France, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It was the sixth stage in this year's Tour de France which was
won by an Italian rider.
</P>
<P>
Commesso beat compatriot Marco Serpellini by two seconds after
they had broken clear some 39 kilometers from the finish line of
the stage.
</P>
<P>
Mariano Piccoli of Italy came in third two minutes later. Tour
leader Lance Armstrong of the United States arrived with the main
pack, 22 minutes and 23 seconds after Commesso. 
</P>
</TEXT>
