<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Make Better Use of Water Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia is beefing up effort
to make better use of water resources throughout the country,
Ethiopian News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government has approved a water policy deemed to
promote the sustainable utilization of water sources of the
country, Water Resources Minister Shiferaw Jarsso was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Regional states would translate the national water policy into
action based on their objective local realities, he said.
</P>
<P>
On reason to implement the new water resources strategy,
Shiferaw said that the various water projects undertaken in
Ethiopia over the last 40 years had not produced the desired
result.
</P>
<P>
The majority of the potable and irrigation projects carried out
over the last four decades had not been able to effectively
respond to the basic needs of the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, less than 10 percent of the water
projects undertaken to date are functional. "The remaining have
gone out of service largely due to lack of maintenance services
and facilities."  
</P>
</TEXT>
