<DOCNO> XIE19990718.0029 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Undermining Cross-Straits Relations Inadmissible" (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Lee Teng-hui is taking a very
dangerous step by redefining cross-Straits relations as "state-to-
state", which reveals his intention to separate Taiwan from China,
according to a commentary from Xinhua News Agency today.
</P>
<P>
The article stressed that the "one China" principle is the
foundation and prerequisite for the development of cross-Straits
relations and the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Lee has strayed too far down the separatist path and has put at
risk the future of Taiwan and its people, said the article, adding
that Lee's remarks have plunged cross-Straits relations, which
have been developing smoothly in recent years, into unprecedented
difficult situation.
</P>
<P>
As early as in 1979, the Standing Committee of China's National
People's Congress proposed in its Letter to the Taiwan Compatriots:
"The 'one China' principle and opposition to independence for
Taiwan should be the common stand and foundation for the
development of cross-Straits relations".
</P>
<P>
In 1995, Deng Xiaoping put forward the creative framework of "
peaceful reunification, and one country with two systems" for the
purpose of solving the Taiwan problem, with the prerequisite of
one China.
</P>
<P>
Also in 1995, Chinese President Jiang Zemin stressed in his
eight-point proposition for promoting the peaceful reunification
of the motherland that the "one China" principle is the foundation
and prerequisite for realizing the peaceful reunification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Jiang again stressed the "one China" principle and strong
opposition to "independence for Taiwan", as well as "two Chinas"
or "one China, one Taiwan" in the report of the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
He stated that no foreign forces will be allowed to interfere
in the Taiwan issue nor any forces allowed to change by any means
the fact that Taiwan is an inalienable part of China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990718.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Undermining Cross-Straits Relations Inadmissible" (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1992 the Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits
and Taiwan's Straits Exchanges Foundation reached a common
understanding that both sides of the Taiwan Straits should abide
by the "one China" principle, and they conducted a series of
consultations, exchanges and dialogs based on this principle.
</P>
<P>
To sum up, through 20 years of contacts and exchanges, the two
sides of the Taiwan Straits witnessed a steady development in
their relations.
</P>
<P>
Facts prove that Lee Teng-hui is a person who is trying to
hinder the historical trend of moving toward reunification of the
motherland. His remarks in defiance of the "one China" principle
have seriously affected the relations between the two sides of the
Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Prior to stepping down from office, Lee Teng-hui has made
separatist remarks which will bring nothing but harm the interests
of the Taiwan compatriots.
</P>
<P>
The article warned Lee Teng-hui sternly that on no account
should the "one China" principle be undermined, or he will bear
the responsibility for it and become a historical sinner by trying
to separate Taiwan from China.
</P>
<P>
The article said that it is the sublime wish of the Chinese
people on both sides of the Taiwan Straits to realize peaceful
reunification of the motherland, which conforms to their
fundamental interests.
</P>
<P>
It is always a solid policy of the Chinese government and
people to develop cross-Straits relations and promote peaceful
reunification of the motherland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990718.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Business Welcomes IMF Promise of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's business community
Sunday welcomed the move by the International Monetary Fund (IMF)
to disburse 200 million U.S. dollars in the next 14-months to
Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
President of the Indigenous Business Development Community Ben
Mucheche said, "We are very delighted that the IMF has realized
there is need of this facility which has been long overdue.
Although it is not enough and falls far too short of what we
require here, we hope the money will help the economy to improve."
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Mail reported that the IMF had finally agreed to
disburse 200 million U.S. dollars over the next 14 months starting
from two weeks' time under a new balance of payments support
agreement.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive of Zimbabwe National Chamber of Commerce wOnder
Maisiri said, "This is good news for Zimbabwe, particularly the
business community which will derive a wide range of financial
benefits which will sustain the economy of Zimbabwe more
vibrantly."
</P>
<P>
He said, "Businesses have suffered and a number of companies
have closed down as inflation continues to rise and commercial
interest rates are crippling."
</P>
<P>
He appealed to Zimbabweans and the country's leaders to seize
the opportunity to redirect the country's economic endeavors which
had so far been fragmented.
</P>
<P>
He said there had been no concerted effort to add value to the
country's economic activities and that jobs had been lost and
people urged to tighten their belts.
</P>
<P>
The agreement puts an end to almost two years of waiting by
Zimbabwe to receive the balance of payments support from the IMF
expected to shore up the country's ailing economy, strengthen the
local currency and unlock more than 300 million U.S. dollars
support from other international donors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
