<HEADLINE> Macao, HK, Zhuhai Pupils Have Language Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 18 (Xinhua) -- A total of 14 primary school pupils
from Macao, Hong Kong and Macao's neighbor Zhuhai City took part
in a language contest here this afternoon to show their
proficiency in Chinese Mandarin and English.
</P>
<P>
During the tryout, the participants were required to use one
minute introducing themselves in Chinese or English, and then use
three minutes to read aloud two poems respectively in Chinese and
English.
</P>
<P>
In the course of the contest, the pupils from Zhuhai seemed to
be more fluent in speaking Chinese and those coming from Hong Kong
had a better capability in English.
</P>
<P>
Four pupils from Zhuhai and one from Macao were qualified to
enter the final contest, in which the students were asked to
deliver a short speech on what they would become in the future.
</P>
<P>
In the end, the best contestant was awarded to Xia Xin, a six-
grader from Zhuhai City.
</P>
<P>
The contest was organized by three youth organizations in the
three places. They had arranged one such contest in Zhuhai last
year, and the third will be held in Hong Kong next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
