<HEADLINE> Egypt Affirms Adherence to One-China Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Egypt said on Sunday that it
consistently adheres to the one-China policy and will never
establish official relations with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Chinese Ambassador to Egypt, An Huihou,
Egyptian Assistant Foreign Minister for Asian Affairs, Nagi Al-
Ghadrifi, stressed that Egypt maintains the one-China policy as
its constant position on dealing with the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Al-Ghadrifi affirmed to An that his country's policy on the
Taiwan issue will remain unchanged regardless of any remarks made
by any person.
</P>
<P>
Lee Teng-hui, leader of the Taiwanese authorities, claimed in
an interview with a German radio early this month that the Taiwan
authorities had defined the cross-Straits relations as "state-to-
state, or at least special state-to-state relations."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has condemned Lee's remarks as an utter
exposure of his premediated intentions to divide China's territory
and sovereignty, and create "two Chinas," "one China, one Taiwan"
or "Taiwan's independence."
</P>
<P>
Egypt and China enjoy close, solid and friendly relations of
cooperation and the leaders of the two countries maintain
coordination and consultations on regional and international
issues, Al-Ghadrifi said.
</P>
<P>
He underlined that any provocative remarks made by the Taiwan
authorities will not shake Egypt's firm stance on the one-China
policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
