<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Fernando Vargas of the United
States stopped his countryman Raul Marguez in the 11th round to
retain his IBF junior middleweight title Saturday night in
Stateline, Nevada,the United States.
</P>
<P>
Vargas kept his record perfect, winning his 17th straight fight.
Referee stopped the fight in the 11th round as Vargas hit Marquez
along the ropes.
</P>
<P>
Vargas, 21, a 1996 Olympian, opened cuts around both of Marquez
's eyes in making his second successful defense of the title he
gained last December.
</P>
<P>
Marquez, 27, a 1992 Olympian who held the title for eight
months in 1997, fell to 30-2. 
