<HEADLINE> Malaysian Chinese Association General Assembly Ends on Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The 46th Malaysian Chinese
Association (MCA) general assembly ended here on Sunday, resolving
to fully support the leadership of Prime Minister Datuk Seri Dr.
Mahathir Mohamad and his deputy Datuk Seri Abdullah Ahmad Badawi.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 delegates attended the two-day assembly which
was opened by Dr. Mahathir at the Wisma MCA here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The party also pledged to fully support all the efforts taken
by the government to ensure political stability, social harmony
and economic progress in the country.
</P>
<P>
In view of the MCA's success in consolidating the party and in
strengthening ties with the Chinese community, the assembly
resolved to fully support MCA president Datuk Seri Dr. Ling Liong
Sik and his deputy, Datuk Lim Ah Lek, to continue to lead the
party into the new century.
</P>
<P>
It also resolved to further strengthen the party by boosting
its membership to one million by next year.
</P>
<P>
On the economy, the delegates recognized the measures taken by
the government to revive the economy without assistance from the
International Monetary Fund.
</P>
<P>
They urged the government to help expedite the processing of
applications for the various SMI (small and medium-scale
industries) funds.
</P>
<P>
On education, the assembly urged the authorities to give more
opportunities for non-Bumiputera students to pursue courses in
local universities.
</P>
<P>
It also called on the government to draw up a comprehensive
plan to overcome problems in Chinese primary schools, including
the shortage of teachers.
</P>
<P>
On social matters, the delegates urged the police to take
effective steps to tackle social problems such as secret society
activities in schools, drug abuse, domestic violence, abduction of
young girls and child abuse.
</P>
<P>
There was also a resolution on agriculture which called on the
government to open up more land and to relax the conditions and
expedite the processing of applications for agricultural purposes.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
