<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Condemns Lee Teng-hui's Separatist Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan and
Overseas Chinese Affairs Committee of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
issued a statement today severely condemning Lee Teng-hui's
separatist remarks.
</P>
<P>
Lee said on July 9 in an interview with a German radio station
that cross-Straits relations should be defined as "state-to-state,
or at least special state-to-state relations". This was echoed
later by other Taiwanese officials, who said that cross-Straits
talks are "bilateral talks between two states".
</P>
<P>
Lee's separatist remarks have posed a great threat to cross-
Straits relations and harmed the stability of cross-Straits
relations, in disregard of the desire of all Chinese in the world
to seek peaceful reunification, according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement reiterated that there is only one China in the
world, and Taiwan is an inalienable part of China.
</P>
<P>
The two sides across the Taiwan Straits have not yet become
unified, but the status of Taiwan as an inalienable part of China
has never been changed, and the "one-China" principle has been
recognized by most countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
Lee's separatist remarks have been widely criticized by people
on both sides of the Taiwan Straits and by overseas Chinese, while
arousing alarm among Taiwan's people and leading to a downward
plunge of Taiwan's stock market.
</P>
<P>
The international community has also expressed disagreement
with the assertions of "independence for Taiwan", "Two Chinas" and
"One China, One Taiwan".
</P>
<P>
The committee repeatedly warned both Lee and the Taiwan
authorities not to underestimate the firm resolve of the Chinese
government to safeguard state sovereignty, dignity and territorial
integrity or the courage and strength of the Chinese people to
fight against separatism and "independence for Taiwan".
</P>
<P>
Lee must stop playing with fire and stop all activities aimed
at separating Taiwan from the motherland, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement also expressed the intention to increase
exchanges with all parties and groups, and people of all walks of
life in Taiwan on the basis of the policies of "peaceful
reunification" and "one country, two systems", in order to improve
mutual understanding and to hasten the peaceful reunification of
the motherland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
