<HEADLINE> Chinese in Macao Condemn Lee's Separatist Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Returned Overseas
Chinese in Macao held a meeting Saturday to condemn the separatist
remarks by Taiwan's Lee Teng-hui.
</P>
<P>
The participants in the meeting indignantly denounced Lee Teng-
hui's attempt to split the motherland, warning that "the one who
plays with fire will get burnt."
</P>
<P>
The separatist scheme of Lee Teng-hui has seriously harmed
cross-Strait relations and stability, undermined the process of
peaceful reunification, and ignored the desire of the Taiwanese
people to seek peace and development, the participants said.
</P>
<P>
They noted that for a long period, the central government has
been exerting unremitting efforts together with people throughout
the country to push forward the great cause of reunifying the
country. To settle the Taiwan question and achieve the complete
reunification of the motherland are the strong aspiration and
sacred mission of all Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
The participants reiterated their view that there is only one
China in the world, and that Taiwan is an inalienable part of
China. Any actions of deliberate separatism will be vehemently
opposed by all Chinese people including the compatriots in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The participants said that they would persistently hold the "
one-China" stance, firmly safeguard national sovereignty and
territorial integrity, and fight against any separatist actions.
</P>
