<HEADLINE> China's Civil Aviation Does Well In June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The latest figures show that the
gross transportation turnover, passenger traffic volume, and
freight and mail traffic volume of China's civil aviation sector
last month rose by 16.5 percent, 7.3 percent and 27.1 percent,
respectively, on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Insiders attributed the significant increase to the measures
adopted by the Civil Aviation Administration of China to reduce
the number of redundant airplanes and flights over the past few
months.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that transportation on international
flights and those to Hong Kong and Macao continued to greatly
improve last month, with the gross turnover and passenger traffic
volume increasing by 30 percent and 20 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The domestic passenger traffic volume also increased by 5.3
percent in June.
</P>
<P>
Insiders noted that, due to the sluggish domestic market, it
will still be difficult for China's civil aviation to reach its
target projected earlier this year to turn losses into a profit.
</P>
</TEXT>
