<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Members Contribute to Improvement of Tibet's Ecology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- A survey of the ecological
environment of the Tibet Autonomous Region in southwest China has
attributed the good water quality of rivers and lakes in Tibet to
afforestation efforts made by local People's Liberation Army
garrisons during the past four decades.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the Tibet Military Area Command mobilized
three million officers and men and used 40,000 motor vehicles for
the campaign to plant trees and grass in Tibet during this period.
</P>
<P>
Members of PLA garrisons planted 20 million trees and four
million square meters of grass, and built 158 shelter belts and
420 orchards over the past 40 years. They have also reclaimed
nearly 667,000 hectares of barren land.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the green area created by PLA members
accounts for 70 percent of Tibet's total cultivated green area.
</P>
