<HEADLINE> China's New Licensing Arrangement to Prevent Money Laundering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Individual Chinese have to apply
for a new license if they plan to take more than 10,000 U.S.
dollars worth of foreign exchange in cash out of the country,
starting August 1.
</P>
<P>
According to a new ruling issued by the State Administration of
Foreign Exchange (SAFE) and the General Administration of Customs,
China will begin using its new License for Taking Foreign Exchange
Overseas, with the old version becoming invalid as of September 1.
</P>
<P>
A SAFE spokesman says that the purpose of the new rule is to
prevent illegal activities like money laundering and smuggling of
foreign exchanges.  
