<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ICBC Loans Increase 90 Billion Yuan in First Half of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial Bank
of China (ICBC) announced today that its loans increased 94.2
billion yuan in the first half of this year, some 12.4 billion
yuan more than in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
President of the ICBC Liu Tinghuan said that 37 percent of the
bank's loans have been granted to fixed assets and the housing
sector, compared with only four percent in the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The development of automobile, durable goods, and small
mortgage loans has also made significant progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the ICBC saw a record increase in savings in the
first six months, with domestic currency savings increasing 228.8
billion yuan, 109 billion yuan more than that of the same period
of last year.
</P>
<P>
Foreign exchange savings also enjoyed an increasing momentum,
he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that the bank's new progress in the first half of this
year also includes the successful launching of its capital
remittance settlement system, the expansion of its online business
outlets from 5,000 to more than 8,000, as well as a series of new
internal control measures to minimize financial risks.
</P>
<P>
In the second half of this year, the ICBC will continue to
support selected quality enterprises and projects, and will make
efforts to develop new credit businesses, Liu said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
