<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts '99 World Management Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- More than 500 Chinese and foreign
scholars, entrepreneurs and managers gathered at the Great Hall of
the People in downtown Beijing today for the opening ceremony of
the '99 World Management Conference.
</P>
<P>
The conference, jointly hosted by the Germany-based
International Federation of Scholars and Academies of Management,
the People's University of China in Beijing and China's National
Natural Science Foundation, features the theme of "economic and
information globalization and the management reform in the 21st
century".
</P>
<P>
Participants of the three-day conference will have discussions
and exchanges on six major topics, namely management science,
management strategy, capital management, enterprise innovation,
management science and technology, and management education and
comprehensive management.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Siwei, vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, China's top legislature, served as the
chairman of the current conference. He is also director of the
management science department of the Chinese National Natural
Science Foundation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
