<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Makinen on Route to Fourth World Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- World champion Tommi Makinen
snatched the New Zealand motor rally on Sunday, coming closer to a
record fourth straight world championship title.
</P>
<P>
Makinen, behind the wheels of a Mitsubishi, got his third win
this season as he led home a Finnish top three sweep with Subaru's
Juha Kankkunen and Toni Gardmeister, in a SEAT, second and third
respectively.
</P>
<P>
It was Makinen's 18th career win and increased his title lead
from four to 11 points over Frenchman Didier Auriol, who finished
fourth for Toyota on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
