<HEADLINE> Team USA Routs Argentina in Pre-Olympic Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Team USA routed Argentina 103-
72 today in the Pre-Olympic Basketball Qualifying Tournament of
the Americas in San Juan, Puerto Rico.
</P>
<P>
After winning their first two first-round games by an average
margin of 40 points, the NBA stars of Team USA clinched the top
spot in Group A by scoring 100 points for the second time in three
contests.
</P>
<P>
Minnesota Timberwolves forward Kevin Garnett led the way with
21 points and 10 rebounds and Miami Heat guard Tim Hardaway added
20 points for the team, which dropped Argentina (1-2) to fourth
place in Group A.
</P>
<P>
The Americans shot an astounding 67 percent (24-of-36) in the
first half while holding Argentina to 28 percent (10-of-36) and
opening a commanding 57-27 lead.
</P>
<P>
San Antonio Spurs forward Tim Duncan sank 7-of-8 shots today en
route to 14 points and eight rebounds.
</P>
<P>
Guards Jason Kidd of the Phoenix Suns and Allan Houston of the
New York Knicks and Seattle SuperSonics forward Vin Baker each
tallied 11 points for Team USA.
</P>
<P>
In the other games, Canada posted an 80-62 victory over Uruguay
in today's Group A game, nailing down second place.
</P>
<P>
The Americans are the only unbeaten team in Group A. In Group B,
unbeaten Puerto Rico clinched first place with its third straight
victory, an 85-71 triumph over winless Panama.
</P>
<P>
The semifinals are Saturday, with the winners earning an
Olympic berth and playing for the gold medal on day later.
</P>
</TEXT>
