<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Search for Missing Plane Brings Fears of Another Kennedy Tragedy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Hope dimmed late Saturday for
John F. Kennedy Jr., son of the former U.S. president, his wife
and sister-in-law, as darkness descended on the waters off Martha'
s Vineyard in Massachusetts State where their plane went down.
</P>
<P>
Fears grew that America's most renowned political family had
suffered another ghastly tragedy. Debris washed ashore, but there
was no sign of life.
</P>
<P>
The couple went to Massachusetts State to attend the wedding of
the young Kennedy's cousin. The plane left an airfield in New
Jersey State at 8:45 p.m. (local time) Friday.
</P>
<P>
"I can tell you miraculous stories of people surviving," said
Rear Admiral Richard M. Larrabee, first Coast Guard district
commander, at a late afternoon news conference in Massachusetts."I
can tell you in previous cases like this, we've searched as many
as three or four days. We're not ready to give up on this yet."
</P>
<P>
While the visual aerial search was suspended for the night late
Saturday, three helicopters with infrared sensors and Coast Guard
boats with bright lights and a sonar-equipped submersible
continued searching overnight in the dark, Coast Guard officials
said.
</P>
<P>
Coast Guardsmen and Air National Guardsmen were equipped with
night vision goggles, and an Air National Guard C-130 airplane was
flying through the night coordinating the search effort, said
Coast Guard Petty Officer Todd Burgun.
</P>
<P>
Authorities said National Transportation Safety Board
investigators already were at work on the Vineyard.
</P>
<P>
The Coast Guard identified the plane as a single-engine, six-
seat Piper Saratoga II HP, acquired recently by the Kennedy. The
plane is known in the aviation industry as a high-performance
airplane with a good safety record.
</P>
<P>
Kennedy, 38, is the only surviving son of the 35th president,
and was born just two months before his father's inauguration.
</P>
<P>
His father's assassination immediately thrust him into the
public eye with the poignant photo of the little boy saluting as
his funeral procession passed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990718.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inflation Falls Below 2 Percent In India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- For the first time in 17 years,
Indian annual rate of inflation fell to 1.83 percent for the week
ended July 3, due mainly to a steady decline in vegetable prices.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics published here on Sunday showed that the
index for vegetables during the week was at 430.6 as against 699.1
in the correspondent period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The rate of increase in prices, based on the wholesale price
index, declined by 0.20 percentage points to 1.83 percent in the
week from 2.03 percent a week earlier.
</P>
<P>
The falling trend was also helped by a slackness in industrial
demand, which kept the prices of manufactured products low.
</P>
<P>
This is the lowest inflation rate since August 1982 when it
touched 1.66 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the current fiscal, prices of agricultural produce remained
rocksteady due to a bumper crop harvest in the last season.
</P>
<P>
Foodgrain production in 1998-99 is estimated to have touched a
record 205 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Despite the record lows in inflation, the retail prices
measured by consumer price index for urban non-manual employees
are still ruling high at 6.1 percent in June compared to a monthly
average of 2.78 percent.
</P>
<P>
Among the three major groups in the wholesale price index,
primary articles is at 1.38 percent, followed by manufactured
products at 1.73 percent, and fuel, power, light and lubricants at
3.76 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
