<HEADLINE> UAE to Keep Lid on U.K. Beef </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)
will maintain its ban on import of British beef despite the
European Commission's decision to allow Britain U.K. to export
cattle meat.
</P>
<P>
The issue of lifting the ban on British beef must be taken up
by the UAE's General Secretariat of Municipalities (GSM), the Gulf
News daily on Sunday quoted Dubai Municipality sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, there is no scheduled meeting for
the GSM at the moment due to the unavailibility of most officials
who are on holiday.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission on Wednesday lifted the world-wide ban
on British beef, which was imposed three years ago over fears of
mad cow disease.
</P>
<P>
In the UAE, the ban was imposed in April 1996. The
UAE's major sources of beef imports, currently, are Australia,
India and New Zealand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
