<HEADLINE> ASEAN Factsheet (1): Brief Introduction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Singapore is hosting the 32nd
ASEAN Ministerial Meeting on July 23-24. A brief introduction to
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) follows:
</P>
<P>
ASEAN was established on August 8, 1967 with the signing of the
ASEAN Declaration, otherwise known as the Bangkok Declaration, by
the ministers of foreign affairs of Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Singapore and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN later expanded to include Brunei in 1984, Vietnam in
1995, Laos and Myanmar in 1997, and Cambodia in April 1999.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN region spans an area of some 5.48 million square
kilometers where 14 official languages are spoken and about seven
religions adhered to. And its population is estimated at 494.84
million.
</P>
<P>
Organization structure of ASEAN comprises summit meeting (the
highest authority of ASEAN bringing together the heads of
government of the member countries), ministerial meetings,
standing committee, secretariats, committees and senior officials'
meetings.
</P>
<P>
Founded in Bangkok on the principal objective of accelerating
economic growth and increasing the stability of the Southeast
Asian region, ASEAN has grown into one of the most dynamic
political and economic organizations of developing countries and
has been playing a significant role in maintaining peace and
stability and helping promote economic development in the region.
</P>
<P>
Papua New Guinea became an observer of ASEAN in 1995 and is now
the only observer nation of ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN has 10 dialogue partners -- Australia, Canada, China, the
European Union, India, Japan, Russia, New Zealand, South Korea and
the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990718.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Heists Rise in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Seventy-one bank branches
have encountered holdups in the past six and a half months in
Argentina, with the robbers making away with more than 11 million
pesos (11 million U.S. dollars), doubling the figure in terms of
money for 1998, police said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Thieves seem to like Tuesdays and Wednesdays, as 35 of the 71
holdups were made on those days of the week, according to police
statistics.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, 126 bank branches were robbed in the country, with a
booty of more than 6 million pesos (6 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The frequency of heists, which demonstrated that the robbers
knew in detail the movements of the bank and the location of the
vault, made investigators suspect police participation in those
robberies.
</P>
<P>
A public prosecutor one month ago detained a police officer
accused of taking part in the holdup of a bank in the city of
Pilar, some 50 kilometers northwest of Buenos Aires, from which
the thieves took 33,000 pesos (33,000 dollars).
</P>
<P>
The most recent robbery was carried out last Tuesday in the
Banco Nacion branch in Buenos Aires City, after a shoot-out with
police.
</P>
<P>
Six of the 71 bank robberies perpetrated this year were
resolved by police, although only in two cases the stolen money
was recovered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
