<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Factsheet (2): FMM, ARF, PMC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 18 (Xinhua) -- From July 23 to 28, the 32nd
Ministerial Meeting of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN), the Sixth ASEAN Regional Forum (ARF) and the ASEAN Post
Ministerial Conferences (PMC) will take place in Singapore,
ASEAN's rotating chairman this year.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN Ministerial Meeting (AMM) comprising ministers of
foreign affairs of the member states, meets annually in each
member country in turn to formulate policy guidelines and
coordinate ASEAN activities.
The 32nd ASEAN Ministerial meeting is scheduled for July 23-24.
</P>
<P>
This meeting is followed by the ASEAN Regional Forum (ARF),
where ASEAN foreign ministers meet with their counterparts from
countries that are dialogue partners as well as from other
countries.
</P>
<P>
ARF, which, initiated in 1993, serves as a multilateral
consultative forum aimed at promoting preventive diplomacy and
confidence building among the nations in the region. The first
meeting of the ARF was held in July 1994. ARF is currently
attended by the ten ASEAN member countries -- Brunei, Cambodia,
Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore,
Thailand and Vietnam, one observer Papua New Guinea and ten ASEAN
dialogue partners -- Australia, Canada, China, the European Union,
India, Japan, New Zealand, Russia, South Korea and the United
States. The 6th ARF is scheduled for July 26.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN Post Ministerial Conferences (PMC) will be held on
July
27-28 between the ten ASEAN members and its ten dialogue partners.
There will be a plenary session and separate individual sessions
between the ASEAN members and each dialogue partner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
