<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil, Argentina Move Towards Auto Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Brazil and Argentina are
advancing towards an agreement on a common automotive scheme that
is scheduled to be in force next January, said a sector spokesman
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The new mechanism will permit "a well-administered market" of
motor vehicles in the region, mainly in Brazil and Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The scheme, based on establishing quotas agreed upon by car
makers of the two countries, will take effect during a four-year
period, from 2000 to 2004.
</P>
<P>
The quotas will be expanded gradually until a true regime of
free trade of vehicles is consolidated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
