<HEADLINE> Highlights of Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin returned to Beijing by special
plane Saturday afternoon after winding up a three-day state visit
to Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
-- Wei Jianxing, a member of the Political Bureau Standing
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee,
attended two drama performances with the theme of anti-corruption
on the evening of July 13 and 16.
</P>
<P>
-- A front-page story features Ningbo, a coastal city in east
China's Zhejiang Province, which has invigorated the local economy
through developing harbor facilities.
</P>
<P>
 Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- A front-page signed article said that persons in power in
Taiwan have recently staged a farce in trying to divide the
motherland, with Lee Teng-hui as its hero. Lee on July 9 redefined
the cross-Straits relations as "state-to-state or at least special
state-to-state relations".
</P>
<P>
-- In the first half of this year, the overall added value
output of the farmers-run township enterprises across China
reached 1.1957 trillion yuan, up 16.5 percent over the same period
of last year, according to the Ministry of Agriculture. The figure
indicates that the performance of the Chinese township enterprises,
which was negatively affected by the Asian Financial Crisis, is
now turning for the better.
</P>
<P>
-- From January to June this year, all exit and entrance check
points affiliated to the Ministry of Public Security recorded some
77.88 million people leaving or entering China, an increase of 14.
45 percent over the same period of 1998 and a new all-time high.
</P>
<P>
China Daily Business Weekly
</P>
<P>
-- China is expected to achieve a balance of international
payments this year despite a shrinking trade surplus and a falling
overseas investment inflow, officials and experts say.
</P>
<P>
-- After slogging through the bumpy first half of the year,
China is determined to continue its strenuous efforts to prevent
declines in exports and foreign investment inflows this year.
</P>
<P>
-- China has decided to overhaul its tax agency sector to
improve the image of tax agent institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
