<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombia Shaken by 5.4 Degree Earthquake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake
registering 5.4 on the Richter scale shook the central region of
Colombia on Saturday, causing no serious damage, said a Colombian
Seismological Institute spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The tremor, which also affected the Colombian capital but with
less intensity, occurred at 07:21 local time, with its epicenter
located in the Sativasur village in the south of the Boyaca
department.
</P>
<P>
Damage and cracking were reported in five houses, the church, a
school and a hospital in the village, but nobody was hurt because
the residents ran out of their houses at the moment of the quake
and gathered at safe places.
</P>
<P>
Located on the seismic strip, Sativasur was shaken on January
25 by a quake of six on the Richter scale that left 1,000 persons
killed and 4,000 injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
