<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, July 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Three people were killed as a Life Flight medical
helicopter crashed southwest of Houston City in Texas State of the
United States Saturday, reports reaching here said. It wasn't
known if there were any survivors. (US-Helicopter-Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The Ulster Unionist leader David Trimble Saturday
gave the strongest of indications that he will not stand down as
Northern Ireland First Minister.
</P>
<P>
In an interview for a BBC Radio program, Trimble said that
despite the resignation of Deputy First Minister Seamus Mallon,
for him to do the same could send a signal that the political
process was disintegrating. (UK-N.Ireland-Trimble)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Taliban senior official responsible for the
foreign affairs Mulla Mohammad Hasan will lead a delegation in the
forthcoming meeting of the "Six Plus Two" group in Tashkent,
capital of Uzbekistan, informed sources here said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The "Six Plus Two" group comprises Afghanistan's six immediate
neighbors including Pakistan, Iran, Uzbekistan, Tajikistan,
Turkmenistan and China plus the United States and Russia. (
Afghanistan-Taliban)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India declared Saturday that intruders found on
its side of the so-called Line of Control (LOC) would be "shot and
killed" as the extended deadline for withdrawal of infiltrators
ended this morning.
</P>
<P>
"The deadline for withdrawal has expired this morning and,
therefore, any Pakistan Army soldier or activity observed on our
side of the LOC will be treated as hostile and targeted
accordingly," an Indian army spokesman told the press here. (India-
Pakistan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- A small plane carrying John F. Kennedy Jr., son
of the former U.S. president, was reported missing early Saturday,
and a search was under way off the coast of New York's Long Island,
official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The plane left an airfield in New Jersey State at 8:45 p.m.(
local time) Friday and was believed to be carrying Kennedy and his
wife Carolyn Bessette to Martha's Vineyard in Massachusetts State,
where the Kennedy family was gathering for a wedding. (US-Plane-
Missing) 
</P>
