<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Voeroes Wins Women's Individual Gold, Russia Takes Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Zsuzsanna Voeroes of Hungary on
Saturday won the women's individual title at the 19th Modern
Pentathlon World Championships.
</P>
<P>
Voeroes, the runner-up in Mexico City last year, took the lead
after the third discipline, swimming, and took a 27-second lead
into the final event, running.
</P>
<P>
Finally Voeroes won the gold medal with 5,319 points, 63 points
ahead of the runner-up, Russia's Elisavieta Suvorova.
</P>
<P>
By winning the world title, Zsuzsanna Voeroes also qualified
for next year's Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The women's team gold medal went to Russia for the third
straight year while Britain took home its second straight silver.
Italy got the bronze.
</P>
<P>
Team order was established on the basis of the total individual
scores of the team members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
