<HEADLINE> Arsenal Manager Says Anelka Talks Continue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- English Premier League football
club Arsenal manager Arsene Wenger has insisted negotiations to
sell striker Nicolas Anelka to Lazio are still on.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Italian club's president Sergio Cragnotti said the
deal was "definitively" off, and described the Premiership club as
"stubborn in the negotiations.
</P>
<P>
But Wenger insisted: "All I can tell you is that talks are
going on.
</P>
<P>
"I'm as fed up about this as anyone else because I didn't want
to lose him but we've been forced to sell."
</P>
<P>
Wenger wants the long-running affair to come to an end soon so
he can replace the forward.
</P>
<P>
The Gunners boss confirmed that he is looking for two new
strikers, but denied an immediate interest in Everton star Francis
Jeffers.
</P>
<P>
"I rate him very highly but I feel he needs more experience in
the Premiership before a judgment can be made," said Wenger.
</P>
<P>
"I am looking for two strikers, but I'm not close to securing
anyone yet. If you find two, then give me a call," added the
Frenchman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
