<HEADLINE> Martinez, Habsudova to Meet in Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Conchita Martinez of Spain overcame
France's Sandrine Testud in straight sets on Saturday to enter the
final of the 180,000 dollars Polish Open women's tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Martinez hit powerful topspins and excellent dropshots,
defeating Testud 6-3, 6-3 in the match that lasted 1 1-2 hours.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's final, Martinez will meet Slovakia's Karina
Habsudova, who beat Sylvia Talaia of Croatia 6-3, 6-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
